# Cursor Automations Guide

Cursor Automations run **cloud agents** in the background on schedules or in response to events from GitHub, Slack, Linear, PagerDuty, and webhooks. They continuously monitor and improve your codebase by following your instructions and using configured tools.

**Create automations**: [cursor.com/automations](https://cursor.com/automations)  
**Templates**: [cursor.com/marketplace/automations](https://cursor.com/marketplace/automations)  
**Docs**: [cursor.com/docs/cloud-agent/automations](https://cursor.com/docs/cloud-agent/automations)

---

## Getting Started

1. **Create** the automation at cursor.com/automations or start from a marketplace template
2. **Choose tools** the agent can use (Send to Slack, Comment on PR, Open PR, MCP servers)
3. **Write a prompt** with instructions for the automation
4. **Choose a trigger** (schedule, GitHub event, Slack message, webhook, etc.)
5. **Watch it run** — the agent spins up a cloud sandbox and executes

For scheduled or Slack triggers, you also choose a **repository and branch** (Cursor cannot infer them from a PR).

---

## Triggers

An automation can have **multiple triggers**; it runs when any trigger fires.

| Trigger | Events |
|---------|--------|
| **Scheduled** | Recurring schedule or cron expression. May run with delay but not before indicated time. |
| **GitHub** | CI completed, Push to branch, PR commented/merged/pushed/opened, Draft opened |
| **Slack** | New message in channel (keyword/regex filter optional), Channel created (public channels only) |
| **Webhook** | Private HTTP endpoint — POST to start a run. Connect to CI, monitoring, internal systems. Save automation first to get URL + API key. |
| **Linear** | Issue created, Status changed, End of cycle |
| **PagerDuty** | Incident triggered, acknowledged, resolved; Any incident event |

---

## Tools

| Tool | Purpose |
|-----|---------|
| **Open pull request** | Agent writes code, creates branch, opens PR. Use when automation should make code changes. |
| **Comment on pull request** | Posts review/inline comments. Requires PR trigger. Can approve/request changes if approvals enabled. |
| **Request reviewers** | Agent uses git, memory, etc. to identify domain experts. Requires PR trigger. |
| **Send to Slack** | Sends messages to a channel. Target specific channel or let agent choose. |
| **Read Slack channels** | Read-only access to list and read public channel messages. Use when agent needs context before replying/opening PR. |
| **MCP server** | Connects MCP so agent can use external tools and data. Only connect trusted servers. |
| **Memories** | Agent reads/writes persistent notes across runs. Build agents that improve over time. Disable if handling untrusted input. |

Automations also include the same base tools as cloud agents (computer use, demos, CI fix). See [Cloud agent capabilities](https://cursor.com/docs/cloud-agent/capabilities).

