## Use Cases

### Review and Monitoring

- **Security review** — Trigger on every push to main; audit diff for vulnerabilities; post high-risk findings to Slack
- **Agentic codeowners** — On PR open/push: classify risk (blast radius, complexity, infra impact); auto-approve low-risk; assign reviewers for high-risk
- **Incident response** — PagerDuty trigger → agent uses Datadog MCP to investigate logs, checks recent code changes, posts to on-call Slack with proposed fix PR
- **Find vulnerabilities** — Review PRs for security issues, flag exploitable weaknesses before merge
- **Bugbot-style** — PR opened/updated → automated review (style, correctness, security)

### Chores

- **Weekly summary** — Cron → post Slack digest of merged PRs, bug fixes, tech debt, security/dependency updates
- **Test coverage** — Daily: identify recently merged code needing tests; add tests following conventions; run tests; open PR
- **Bug report triage** — Slack message → check duplicates, create Linear issue via MCP, investigate root cause, attempt fix, reply in thread
- **Clean up feature flags** — Find stale fully-rolled-out flags, remove dead code paths
- **Fix CI failures** — Detect CI failures on main, automatically open fix PRs
- **Generate docs** — Create/update developer docs for recently changed or under-documented code

### External Examples (Rippling)

- **Personal assistant** — Cron every 2h: read Slack (notes, TODOs, Loom), GitHub PRs, Jira; deduplicate; post clean dashboard
- **Slack → Jira** — Create Jira issues from threads
- **Summarize discussions** — Post to Confluence
- **Incident triage, weekly status, on-call handoff**

