## Settings

### Model

Choose which model the agent uses. Same models as cloud agents, tailored for autonomous use.

### Environment

Inherited from [Cloud Agents dashboard](https://cursor.com/dashboard?tab=cloud-agents):

- **Disabled** — Skip dependency install. Use when agent only reads/reviews code.
- **Enabled** — Install dependencies before running. Use when automation needs to build, test, or execute.

Configure env and secrets in Cloud Agents dashboard.

### Permissions

| Scope | Who can view | Who can manage | Billing |
|-------|--------------|----------------|---------|
| **Private** | Only you (admins can view/disable) | Only you | Your usage |
| **Team Visible** | Team members | Only you (admins can disable) | Your usage |
| **Team Owned** | Team members | Team admins only | Team usage pool |

Team Owned automations open PRs as `cursor`; Private open as your GitHub account.

### Identity

- Slack messages sent as Cursor bot
- Private: PRs as your GitHub account
- Team-scoped: PRs as `cursor`; comments/reviews as `cursor`

---

## Billing

Automations create cloud agents; billed per [cloud agent usage](https://cursor.com/docs/models-and-pricing#model-pricing). Allocation depends on permission scope (see table above).

---

## Prompt Tips

- Describe the output format you want
- Set a quality bar for when to open PR, comment, or do nothing
- Include decision rules for different cases
- Reference enabled tools (at-mention or by name)
- Be specific about what to check, change, or produce

